  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;span lang=&quot;EN-US&quot;&#xD;
    style=&quot;FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: 'Times New Roman','serif'; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: ES; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA&quot;>&lt;font&#xD;
     face=&quot;Arial&quot;>To identify the services needed to perform the business processes modeled in the Business Modeling&#xD;
    Discipline, classifying them by type of service.&amp;nbsp;To define the Services Architecture diagram specified in SoaML&#xD;
    identifying participants, services to be provided to other parties and consumed from other parties based on&#xD;
    interchanged messages, and service contracts&amp;nbsp;to define the roles in the services interaction.&lt;/font>&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
